CAPE TOWN - Are you a sports fan? Then you are in for a treat as all DStv customers will be able to access the full complement of SuperSport channels at no extra charge, MultiChoice announced in a statement. Between the 13th of July to the 31st of July, DStv Access, Family, Compact, and Compact Plus customers will receive access to all 13 SuperSport channels. According to MultiChoice, the promotion was its way of thanking customers for their continued support. “Sport has a beautiful way of uniting friends and families, and sometimes even strangers,” said MultiChoice South Africa CEO Calvo Mawela. “This is our way of thanking our customers for their support.” This open period will let DStv customers watch the FIFA World Cup final and the third-place playoff match, he added. Other important sporting events happening in the same period include the Wimbledon finals, the German and Hungarian Formula One Grand Prix, and the Super Rugby playoffs. Additionally, customers will also be able to stream SuperSport channels live on DStv Now. - BUSINESS REPORT ONLINE